l of analysis. The individual chapters vividly illuminate the ways in which Christian politics operate across a wide scale, from interpersonal relations to national and global interconnections.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aChristian sectsxOceania. 0aChristian sectszOceania. 0aChristian sects. 0aChristianity and politicsxOceania. 0aChristianity and politicszOceania. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh1 aBarker, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEriksen, Annelin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHandman, Courtney, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKeane, Webb, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcDougall, Debra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcDougall, Debra, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRobbins, Joel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aScott, Michael W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTomlinson, Matt, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTomlinson, Matt, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWhite, Geoffrey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311099828340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978085745745540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780857457455423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780857457455/original  a978-3-11-099828-3  Berghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_